{
  "stem": "20088.9",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, we could move in there, which was extremely lucky, because most people had lost everything.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- and there were not that many people who had come back, unfortunately.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But they had to really find a new-- new place to live, and it was very different.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was a lot of war damage, as well, in Amsterdam.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So Otto Frank, for instance, he went to live with Miep, who was an employee who used to help hide his family.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was around the corner from us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So one day, the bell rang, and Otto stood there, and the Red Cross had sent information out of people who had come back, because it was all registered, and so that people could get in touch with each other to find out if they knew about their family or friends.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So he came to us and asked if he had perhaps seen his family.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then be told him that we had met him, and we had talked about it, and he hadn't-- he had forgotten about it.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He couldn't remember at all that he had seen my mother or me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he became a very good friend, then.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He came often to us and talked to us, and [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] still hoping that our families would come back.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then, about six weeks after we had come back to Holland, we got notices from the Red Cross.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We got the notice that Heinz and [?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Fetty ?] had died in Mauthausen, beginning of May, just a few days before the liberation.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And Otto Frank got notices that his wife had died in Auschwitz and Anne and Margot in Bergen-Belsen-- not to expect day, sometime in March or April, so it was well quite late in the war.",
      "word_count": 36
    }
  ],
